---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { companyStats } from '../data/company-stats';
const { entity, registeredOffice } = companyStats.legal;
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Pacific Ocean Tech collects, uses, and protects personal information."
  slug="privacy-policy"
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p>{entity} (trading as "Pacific Ocean Tech," "POT," "we," "us") provides remote staffing and talent placement services to business clients worldwide, with service delivery from our team centre at {companyStats.address.oneLiner}. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle personal information when you visit our website, request a consultation, or engage our services.</p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We may collect: contact details (name, email, phone, company); hiring requirements and job descriptions; billing and contract information; website usage data (cookies, IP address, pages viewed); and communications you send us (email, forms, live chat).</p>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to inquiries and provide staffing proposals</li>
    <li>To match clients with vetted professionals and manage engagements</li>
    <li>To process payments and maintain business records</li>
    <li>To improve our website, services, and security</li>
    <li>To send service-related notices and, with consent, marketing communications</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal bases (where applicable)</h2>
  <p>We process data based on contract performance, legitimate business interests (e.g., fraud prevention, analytics), legal obligations, and consent where required (e.g., certain marketing cookies).</p>

  <h2>Sharing of information</h2>
  <p>We do not sell personal information. We may share data with: service providers (hosting, email, CRM, payroll partners); professional advisors; authorities when required by law; and client or talent parties as needed to fulfill a staffing engagement under confidentiality obligations.</p>

  <h2>International transfers</h2>
  <p>We operate globally. Data may be processed in India, Australia, New Zealand, the United States, and other countries where we or our providers maintain facilities. We use appropriate safeguards such as contractual clauses where required.</p>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <p>We retain information for as long as needed to provide services, comply with law, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements—typically up to seven years for business records unless a longer period is required.</p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>We implement administrative, technical, and organizational measures including access controls, encryption in transit, and staff training. No method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.</p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, restrict, or port your data, and to object to certain processing. Contact <a href="mailto:privacy@pacificoceantech.com">privacy@pacificoceantech.com</a> to exercise rights. You may lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</p>

  <h2>Australia — Privacy Act 1988 &amp; Australian Privacy Principles</h2>
  <p>For individuals in Australia, we handle personal information in accordance with the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs). You may request access to and correction of your personal information, and may complain about a suspected breach of the APPs. We will respond within a reasonable period; if a complaint is not resolved to your satisfaction, you may contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au">oaic.gov.au</a>. We will notify affected individuals and the OAIC of eligible data breaches as required by the Notifiable Data Breaches scheme.</p>

  <h2>New Zealand — Privacy Act 2020</h2>
  <p>For individuals in New Zealand, we comply with the Privacy Act 2020 and its Information Privacy Principles. You may request access to and correction of your information and complain to the Office of the Privacy Commissioner at <a href="https://www.privacy.org.nz">privacy.org.nz</a>. We will notify the Commissioner and affected individuals of privacy breaches that are likely to cause serious harm.</p>

  <h2>European Economic Area &amp; United Kingdom — GDPR</h2>
  <p>If you are located in the EEA or UK, the EU/UK General Data Protection Regulation applies. Our legal bases are described above. You have the rights of access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, and objection, and the right to withdraw consent at any time without affecting prior processing. You may lodge a complaint with your local supervisory authority. Where we transfer personal data outside the EEA/UK (including to our India team centre), we rely on appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses. To exercise GDPR rights, contact <a href="mailto:privacy@pacificoceantech.com">privacy@pacificoceantech.com</a>.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>Our services are directed to businesses. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 16.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy periodically. Material changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>{entity} — Privacy Office<br />Email: privacy@pacificoceantech.com<br />Registered office: {registeredOffice}<br />Delivery centre: {companyStats.address.oneLiner}</p>
</LegalLayout>
